<item>
            <title>[LU-16115] Linux v5.17 external module build support/workaround</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16115</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v5.16-rc3-26-g129ab0d2d9f3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added quotes around &quot;$(CONFIG_CC_VERSION_TEXT)&quot;, however&lt;br/&gt;
.config stores CONFIG_CC_VERSION_TEXT with quotes thus&lt;br/&gt;
breaking the GNU make Makefile for external modules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to supply a non-quoted value and override the&lt;br/&gt;
value in .config before it is used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
